  <section id="privacy-policy" class="section bg-white">
    <div class="container maxw py-16 md:py-20 prose prose-neutral">
      <h1 class="h1 font-extrabold text-text">Privacy Policy & Recruitment Compliance Notice</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-slate-500">Last updated: October 2025</p>

      <h2>1. Who we are</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>Init Source Ltd</strong> is a UK-based recruitment company acting primarily
        as an Employment Agency for permanent recruitment and, where applicable, an
        Employment Business.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Company name: Init Source Ltd</li>
        <li>Company number: 16785993</li>
        <li>Registered office: 71-75 Shelton Street, Covent Garden, London, WC2H 9JQ, United Kingdom</li>
        <li>Email: <a href="mailto:contact@initsource.co.uk">contact@initsource.co.uk</a></li>
      </ul>

      <h2>2. Data we collect</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Contact details (name, email address, phone number)</li>
        <li>CVs, work history, qualifications, and skills</li>
        <li>Right-to-work and compliance documentation</li>
        <li>Interview notes, screening feedback, and references</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. How we use your data</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Assess suitability for Platform, SRE, and DevOps roles</li>
        <li>Represent candidates to verified employers for genuine opportunities</li>
        <li>Communicate regarding vacancies, interviews, offers, and feedback</li>
        <li>Meet legal, regulatory, and compliance obligations</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We do not sell personal data. Candidate data is shared only with relevant employers
        and only with the candidate's knowledge or consent.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Lawful basis for processing</h2>
      <p>
        We process personal data under the following lawful bases in accordance with UK GDPR:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Legitimate interests (Article 6(1)(f)) for recruitment and placement activities</li>
        <li>Consent where required (e.g. marketing communications), which may be withdrawn at any time</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>5. Data storage, security, and retention</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Data is stored in secure, UK-based systems with access restricted to authorised personnel</li>
        <li>Appropriate technical and organisational safeguards are in place</li>
        <li>Personal data is retained for up to 12 months of inactivity, after which it is securely deleted unless retention is required by law</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>6. Your rights</h2>
      <p>You have the right to request:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Access to your personal data</li>
        <li>Rectification of inaccurate data</li>
        <li>Erasure or restriction of processing</li>
        <li>Objection to processing</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Requests can be made by contacting
        <a href="mailto:contact@initsource.co.uk">contact@initsource.co.uk</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>7. International data transfers</h2>
      <p>
        We do not routinely transfer personal data outside the UK. Where transfers are required,
        appropriate safeguards such as IDTA or Standard Contractual Clauses (SCCs) will be used.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Automated decision-making</h2>
      <p>We do not use solely automated decision-making that produces legal or similarly significant effects.</p>

      <h2>9. Complaints</h2>
      <p>
        If you have concerns about how your data is handled, you may contact us directly.
        You also have the right to lodge a complaint with the UK Information Commissioner's Office (ICO):
        <a href="https://ico.org.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-primary hover:underline">ico.org.uk</a>.
      </p>
